# {{addin_display_name}}

Excel XLL add-in built with Rust.

## Build

```sh
cargo build --release
```

The output is `target/release/{{project-name}}.xll`.

## Install

1. Open Excel
2. Go to **File > Options > Add-ins**
3. At the bottom, select **Excel Add-ins** and click **Go...**
4. Click **Browse...** and select the `.xll` file
5. Click **OK**

## Functions

| Excel Function | Category | Description |
|---------------|----------|-------------|
| `={{crate_name | upcase}}.ADD(a, b)` | {{crate_name}} | Adds two numbers |
| `={{crate_name | upcase}}.MULTIPLY(a, b)` | {{crate_name}} | Multiplies two numbers |
| `=Stats.MEAN(values)` | Stats | Mean of a range |
| `=Sys.VERSION()` | Sys | Returns add-in version |
| `=Sys.NOW_MS()` | Sys | Milliseconds since UNIX epoch (volatile) |


## Test

```sh
cargo build --release
cargo test
```

## Architecture

This project uses:
- [xll-rs](https://crates.io/crates/xll-rs) - XLL runtime
- [xllgen](https://crates.io/crates/xllgen) - Function registration macros
- [xll-utils](https://crates.io/crates/xll-utils) - Export verification
